00:04:37.960 --> 00:04:40.319
• The longest lived domestic cat was named
Creme Puff.

00:04:40.319 --> 00:04:47.870
She lived from August 3, 1967 to August 6,
2005, a span of 38 years and 3 days.

00:04:47.870 --> 00:04:51.470
This is well over double the normal life span
for domestic cats, which is typically around

00:04:51.470 --> 00:04:55.819
12-14 years for males and 13-15 years for
females.

00:04:55.819 --> 00:05:00.100
Interestingly, the owner of Creme Puff, Jake
Perry, also raised a sphynx cat which was

00:05:00.100 --> 00:05:06.830
born in 1964 and didn’t die until 1998,
a span of 34 years and 2 months.

00:05:06.830 --> 00:05:09.710
The cat’s name was “Grandpa Rexs Allen”.

00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:13.629
Why Perry’s two cats lived so long isn’t
entirely known, however, he didn’t usually

00:05:13.629 --> 00:05:15.279
feed them store bought cat food.

00:05:15.279 --> 00:05:20.229
Rather, he raised them on a variety of “natural”
foods; prominent among these foods were: bacon,

00:05:20.229 --> 00:05:23.169
eggs, asparagus, and broccoli, among other
things.

00:05:23.169 --> 00:05:27.389
This can be a somewhat dangerous practice
normally as cats require certain nutrients

00:05:27.389 --> 00:05:30.379
they won’t always get if they are just eating
“human” food.

00:05:30.379 --> 00:05:34.629
For instance, cats will go blind fairly quickly
(and permanently) if they don’t get enough

00:05:34.629 --> 00:05:36.460
taurine, found in muscle.

00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:40.629
Cats also require a high amount of protein
and calcium to maintain proper health.

00:05:40.629 --> 00:05:44.849
This high amount of protein consumed by cats
is thought to be why dogs like cat poop so

00:05:44.849 --> 00:05:46.460
much, with it being very protein-rich.

00:05:46.460 --> 00:05:53.330
• The documented record for the most kittens
born to one cat is currently held by a cat

00:05:53.330 --> 00:05:54.330
named “Dusty”.

00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:59.849
She gave birth to 420 kittens in her lifetime
and even had a litter at the very old age

00:05:59.849 --> 00:06:03.930
(for a cat) of 18 years old.

00:06:03.930 --> 00:06:08.159
• The most kittens in one litter is 14,
a feat accomplished by a cat named Bluebell.

00:06:08.159 --> 00:06:14.419
Amazingly, all 14 kittens survived, which
is rare in large litters of kittens.

00:06:14.419 --> 00:06:19.050
• The smallest adult cat on record was named
Tinker Toy. Tinker Toy as an adult cat weighed

00:06:19.050 --> 00:06:25.099
just one pound, eight ounces and measured
in at just 2.75 inches tall and 7.5 inches

00:06:25.099 --> 00:06:26.099
long.

00:06:26.099 --> 00:06:31.159
• The heaviest cat in the world was 46 pounds
and named Himmy.

00:06:31.159 --> 00:06:46.959
This cat had a waistline of 33 inches.

